reviews.snippet:
My sister dined here last week and told me after that the dish was delicious. She then realized the day after that she left her tote bag at the restaurant. Inside it was her purse containing 4 credit cards, $, and ¥.

Unfortunately the restaurant closed that day, so we asked the hotel staff where we stayed to call the restaurant later.

The next day, we were handed the bag as it was. Really grateful for the restaurant's staff who were honest and helpful. Also to ANA Intercontinental hotel's staff who were very supportive.

I hope the restaurant succeeds forever. Will visit again when we have a chance later. Thank you so much!
